      • invoke

        public AzuquaResponse invoke(String json)
                      throws NoSuchAlgorithmException,
                             InvalidKeyException,
                             IOException

        Invokes a flo.

        *

        Sets the flo resume id if the FLO that has flo-resume capabilities. When the Flo#invoke method is called, the resume id will be saved as an instance property. This id will be use when the Flo#resume method is called.

        Parameters:
        json - A serialized json.
        Returns:
        Throws:
        IOException - There was a problem establishing a connection to the Azuqua server.
        InvalidKeyException - There was a problem generating the hash for the x-api-hash for the header.
        NoSuchAlgorithmException - The HmacSHA256 algorithm isn't available for use.
